 The sky was black in the moonless night. Even shadows could not be made or seen. If not for the stillness and quiet of forest, Serena would have stayed asleep.<br>
Dark figures matching the night began to mill around her new home with Hercules. And the former hind's senses went on alert. Quickly, Serena rose out of her bed and fumbled for her clothing. Then she grabbed a dagger that she had always kept near the bed. By the Gods, she thought, we can't Hercules be here now. <br>
Her hand held onto the dagger tightly, her back to the wall and her eyes set upon the doorway. It was like she could feel them massing outside. <br>
Her heart raced as she stood and waited. <br>
Then suddenly there was a crash behind her in the wall. Armored hands grabbed her and pulled her thru the open gash in the home that she shared with Hercules. She screamed and kicked, slashing the dagger to anything it would hit. The figures pulled her out in the dark forests. Until her cries were heard no more.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uherculestlj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hercules TLJ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hero</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/25/01 6:23:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Home</span><hr size=1> The morning sun was rising high as Hercules made his way down the familiar trail home.  A smile on his face and his steps quick.  He was excited to see Serena again.  Then something made his steps quicker and the smile on his face drop.  He ran to the house, where now he was looking thru a large opening in the wall. <br>
&quot;SERENA!&quot;, he yelled and looked around frantic. Quikly he moved thru the gash looking for clues.  The bed was not made and blankets strewn about.  He walked around the house, and then once exhausting all corners back out into the yard angered.  <br>
&quot;SERENA!!!!!!&quot;<br>
Then a glint of something caught his eye and he looked down.  It was Serena's dagger and next to it, a peacock feather. &quot;Hera,&quot; he said not surprised.  Then then he looked up into the sky &quot;HERA!!!!!!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ulionessofhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lioness of Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/25/01 7:32:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> the new prey</span><hr size=1> As Serena was chained and shakled, Sin stood and watched.  Holding onto her spear she shook her head at the woman who wrestled with the guards.<br>
&quot;You know, it is sad.  You gave up being the last of your kind for Hercules,&quot; Sin spoke calmly. &quot;And now look at you.  Life isn't much better now is it?&quot;<br>
The guards let go of Serena and stepped back.  She was now chained to the floor of the temple and glared back at the huntress. &quot;I have nothing to say to you, Sin.&quot;<br>
Sin laughed, for the hind knew the familiar of Hera well.  They were two immortal beings aligned with the Olympians closely.  They had even once been on the same side.  Yet, now that has changed.<br>
