&quot;Welcome Serena to my temple,&quot; She smiled and walked over to Serena.  With a twists of her wrist, suddenly Serena found a power holding her from movement.  Hera walked over to Serena, &quot;Well, my child.  It seems things just don't always turn out how they were planned do they?&quot;<br>
The Queen's blue eyes glance over at Sin and then back to Serena.  A slender hand reached out and ran around Serena's neck and then up her chin as the ice blue eyes glared into Serena's warm ones. &quot;One should never forget their loyalties.  That wasn't smart leave my son, Ares for Hercules.  You were lucky for a time.  I decided your love for Hercules was good.  But, now....&quot; Hera let go of Serena's chin and spun around walking away.<br>
&quot;It seems your little hero had decided to cross me again,&quot; Hera titled her head to look at a large peacock statue in the great room. &quot;And that is a very unwise decision.&quot;<br>
The Queen of the Gods faced Serena.<br>
The hind glared back refusing to speak to Hera.<br>
A cold look with no expression fell upon Hera's face.  &quot;Well, now hind...your loyalties are going to return.  I think I shall return you to Ares, child.&quot;<br>
Hera lifted up a slender hand palm up...her ice blue eyes glaring into Serena's again. Then her wrist flicked in a graceful move and her palm faced down. &quot;Back in time you shall go.  Back to where your destiny lay.&quot;<br>
Serena screamed and fell to the floor crumpled up in a ball.  Her body seemed to glow every now and then until the glow was bright and shinning.  Serena's screams then changed into an odd cry.  One that was quickly recognizable as that of a hind.  Serena stood quickly and found herself on four hooves...and lost.   She was again, the golden hind.<br>
&quot;Now, that is how things are suppose to be.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ulionessofhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lioness of Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/25/01 7:49:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Familiar Grounds</span><hr size=1> As Serena again was the hind, Sin smiled. &quot;Welcome back my friend.&quot;  The Huntress shifted, molding with the air until she was the golden lioness.  <br>
